'''Stoning resistance''' is a [[resistance]] [[property]] that appears in ''[[NetHack]]'', and protects against the effects of [[stoning]].

==Description==
{{main|Stoning}}
Stoning resistance prevents the [[hero]] and [[monster]]s that have the property from being affected by the stoning attacks and properties of the following monsters:

* [[Cockatrice]]s and [[chickatrice]]s, who can turn victims to stone with their touch attacks and hissing, their [[egg]]s, bare-skin contact with their bodies, and bare-skin contact with their [[corpse]]s or flesh from their [[tin]]s
* [[Medusa]], who can turn victims to stone with her [[passive]] [[gaze]] (for the hero only), as well as stoning anyone that consumes her corpse or tin

===Sources===
Stoning resistance is a property that only occurs intrinsically in the following monsters:

* All [[quest nemeses]]
* All [[acidic]] monsters
** {{monsymlink|acid blob}}s and {{monsymlink|gelatinous cube}}s
** {{monsymlink|spotted jellies}} and {{monsymlink|ochre jellies}}
** {{monsymlink|yellow dragon}}s, {{monsymlink|baby yellow dragon}}s and the {{monsymlink|Chromatic Dragon}}
** {{monsymlink|green mold}}s
** {{monsymlink|black naga}}s and {{monsymlink|black naga hatchling}}s
** all {{mcsl|P}}
* all monsters capable of stoning:
** {{monsymlink|chickatrice}}s and {{monsymlink|cockatrice}}s
** {{monsymlink|Medusa}}, who is special-cased to resist all forms of stoning ''except'' her [[reflected]] gaze{{refsrc|src/mhitu.c|2180|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}
* {{monsymlink|gargoyle}}s and {{monsymlink|winged gargoyle}}s
* all {{mcsl|v}}
* all {{mcsl|y}}
* all {{mcsl|E}}
* {{monsymlink|wraith}}s
* {{monsymlink|xorn}}s
* {{monsymlink|skeleton}}s
* {{monsymlink|ghost}}s and {{monsymlink|shade}}s
* {{monsymlink|stone golem}}s - other golems that are petrified will turn into stone golems
* {{monsymlink|sandestin}}s, {{monsymlink|Juiblex}}, {{monsymlink|Death}}, {{monsymlink|Pestilence}}, {{monsymlink|Famine}}, {{monsymlink|mail daemon}}s, and {{monsymlink|djinn}}
* {{monsymlink|lizard}}s, whose meat can cure delayed stoning

The hero can only obtain stoning resistance through [[polymorph]] into any of the listed monsters that are valid polymorph forms. While many of these monsters are flagged as granting stoning resistance when their corpse or tin is eaten, there is [[Deferred feature|no actual feature implemented]] that reads this flag. 

{{upcoming|NetHack 3.7.0|Per {{commit|071d79dce2ad5b8ade17c4dedf6b57c18b273a59}}, ''temporary'' intrinsic stoning resistance can be granted by eating the corpse or tin of the following monsters: acid blobs, chickatrices, cockatrices, gargoyles, winged gargoyles, spotted jellies, ochre jellies, yellow dragons and their babies, green molds, black nagas and their hatchlings, green slimes, xorns, Medusa, lizards, and the Chromatic Dragon.

Extrinsic stoning resistance can be obtained by wearing [[yellow dragon scales]] or [[yellow dragon scale mail]].}}

==Strategy==
Turning into a monster with stoning resistance is a viable method to either prevent stoning when dealing with several footrices, or else to abort delayed stoning inflicted on the hero. Stoning-resistant monsters can also wield footrice corpses&mdash;beware if a hostile stoning-resistant monster picks one up!

